# Netlify / Cloudflare Pages headers file.
#
# The Rust core (rslib) is compiled for Emscripten with pthread emulation, which
# means it needs real Web Workers backed by SharedArrayBuffer (for its SQLite
# storage layer and its tokio/rayon thread pools). SharedArrayBuffer is only
# available on cross-origin-isolated pages, which requires the server to send
# COOP/COEP on every response — including the production static build, which
# vite-plugin-pwa's service worker does not do for you.
#
# vite.config.ts sets the same two headers for the dev server; keep them in sync.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
